message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - The paper involves the use of deep learning analysis for automatic identification of patients with functionally significant coronary artery stenosis using rest coronary CT angiography. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, since the study involves medical imaging and diagnosis, it could also belong to the Medical Imaging (cs.MED) sub-category. Finally, as the paper involves the use of neural networks, it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NEURON) sub-category.
